        <h1>What is Flu?</h1>
    </div>
    <p>
        Flu (Influenza) is a viral infection that attacks your respiratory system — your nose, throat, and lungs.
        The flu is different from a cold. It usually comes on suddenly and can cause mild to severe illness.
    </p>
    <p>
        The flu spreads mainly by droplets made when people with flu cough, sneeze, or talk.
        These droplets can land in the mouths or noses of people who are nearby or possibly be inhaled into the lungs.
    </p>
</div>

